titleStmt.title: M. Harrington's Parallel unparallel'd: or, A demonstration upon it, and the parable opened. Wherein it appears, neither the spirit of the people, nor the spirit of men like Mr. R. but the spirit of God, of Christ, of his people in the Parliament, and adherents to the cause, is the fittest for the government of the Commonwealth, Zach. 4. 6.
